 succeeded in 0ms:
     1	# Phase 9 chunk 9d ŌĆö Web UI evaluator module
     2	
     3	## Goal
     4	
     5	Add the evaluator role to the reference Web UI so a human can claim a
     6	pending `evaluate` task, inspect the trial-under-evaluation, fill in
     7	metrics by hand, and submit the result. Mirrors the structural
     8	contract pinned in chunk 9c (signed session cookies, per-session CSRF,
     9	HTMX progressive enhancement, retry-before-orphan + committed-state
    10	read-back keyed off `submissions_equivalent`) and the per-claim
    11	isolation pattern (`_CLAIMS` keyed on `(session.csrf, task_id)`),
    12	adapted for the evaluator's distinct shape.
    13	
    14	The evaluator differs from the implementer in three load-bearing
    15	ways:
    16	
    17	1. **No git work.** Per `spec/v0/03-roles.md` ┬¦4.3 the evaluator MUST
    18	   NOT mutate the worker branch or the canonical lineage; it reads
    19	   the trial at `trial.commit_sha` out-of-band (`git clone ŌĆ”` /
    20	   `git fetch && git checkout`) and types metrics back into the
    21	   form. The UI does not accept a `commit_sha` from the operator
    22	   and never calls `repo.create_ref` / any plumbing ŌĆö the evaluator
    23	   module mounts unconditionally (no `--repo-path` requirement).
    24	2. **Trial already exists.** No `Phase 1 create_trial` step. The
    25	   evaluator's `EvaluateTask` carries `payload.trial_id` and the
    26	   trial is in `status="starting"` with `commit_sha` set (per
    27	   ┬¦4.1 + chapter 04 ┬¦3.1). Submit becomes the single Phase, with
    28	   form validation up front and `store.submit` as the only mutation.
    29	3. **`status` has three values.** `success` / `error` / `eval_error`
    30	   per ┬¦4.4. Each maps to a different orchestrator-side trial
    31	   transition; `eval_error` keeps the trial in `starting` and may
    32	   be retried by a fresh evaluate task.
    33	
    34	## Non-goals
    35	
    36	- **Operator-side git operations.** Cloning the bare repo, checking
    37	  out the trial, running tests ŌĆö all out-of-band. The UI surfaces
    38	  `trial.commit_sha` + `trial.branch` so the operator knows what to
    39	  check out, but the UI never proxies git.
    40	- **Metric autocomputation.** No "run the evaluator script for me"
    41	  button; chunk 9d is hand-typed metrics only. A scripted-evaluator
    42	  trigger button is a Phase 9e or later concern.
    43	- **Artifact upload by the UI.** The submission's `artifacts_uri` is
    44	  a free-text URI the operator types after uploading their
    45	  diagnostic logs / artifacts somewhere themselves. UI-driven
    46	  artifact upload is Phase 10 (compose stack ships an artifact
    47	  store) at the earliest.
    48	- **A submission-side `description` field.** The evaluator's submission
    49	  shape per `spec/v0/03-roles.md` ┬¦4.4 is `status` / `trial_id` /
    50	  `metrics` / `artifacts_uri` only ŌĆö there is no submission-carried
    51	  `description`. The chunk-9d form deliberately omits a description
    52	  textarea so the UI does not silently drop operator input. The
    53	  implementer-set `trial.description` (per ┬¦3.2 step 3) is read-only
    54	  context surfaced on the draft page.
    55	- **Per-metric optional/required policy at the UI level.** The spec
    56	  (┬¦4.4) says metric keys are a subset of `metrics_schema`; we
    57	  honor the spec exactly (every metric is optional from the UI's
    58	  perspective, validated as a typed value when present), with one
    59	  pragmatic guardrail: **`status=success` requires at least one
    60	  metric value** so the trial isn't a "successful no-signal" black
    61	  hole. `error` and `eval_error` may carry zero metrics.
    62	- **Mutating `trial.metrics` directly from the UI.** That's the
    63	  orchestrator's exclusive write per ┬¦4.2 / ┬¦4.4 / chapter 04 ┬¦4.3.
    64	  The UI calls `store.submit` and the orchestrator's terminal
    65	  transition does the trial write atomically with the event.
    66	
    67	## Backwards-compatibility policy
    68	
    69	Chunk 9d adds new routes (`/evaluator/*`), one new template family,
    70	and one new `parse_evaluate_form` helper. It changes nothing in the
    71	planner or implementer modules, the wire binding, or the storage
    72	backend. The CLI gains no new flag.
    73	
    74	## Tech-stack decision
    75	
    76	Reuse everything chunk 9c established:
    77	
    78	- HTMX 1.9.12 vendored under `static/` for progressive enhancement
    79	  (chunk 9d does not introduce any HTMX-specific behavior ŌĆö every
    80	  route works as a plain form-POST + 303 redirect ŌĆö but the
    81	  evaluator templates extend `base.html` and inherit the
    82	  enhancement layer).
    83	- `itsdangerous`-signed session cookies (`HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`,
    84	  `Path=/`; opt-in `Secure` via `--secure-cookies`).
    85	- Per-session CSRF token validated in constant time on every
    86	  mutating route.
    87	- Closed wire-error vocabulary: `eden://error/wrong-token`,
    88	  `eden://error/illegal-transition`,
    89	  `eden://error/conflicting-resubmission`,
    90	  `eden://error/invalid-precondition`.
    91	
    92	No new dependencies. No new vendored assets.
    93	
    94	## ┬¦A New routes module
    95	
    96	`reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/evaluator.py`,
    97	prefix `/evaluator`. Routes:
    98	
    99	- `GET /evaluator/` ŌĆö list pending `evaluate` tasks (kind=evaluate,
   100	  state=pending) plus a recent-trials context panel and the
   101	  experiment objective.
   102	- `POST /evaluator/{task_id}/claim` ŌĆö claim with TTL (`expires_at =
   103	  now + claim_ttl_seconds`). Stash `(claim_token, trial_id)` keyed
   104	  on `(session.csrf, task_id)` in an in-process `_CLAIMS` dict.
   105	  `trial_id` is read from the *task payload*, not generated; see
   106	  ┬¦A.2.
   107	- `GET /evaluator/{task_id}/draft` ŌĆö render the draft form (read-
   108	  only trial context + per-metric inputs + status radio + optional
   109	  artifacts_uri + optional description).
   110	- `POST /evaluator/{task_id}/submit` ŌĆö validate, then submit with
   111	  retry-before-orphan + read-back. See ┬¦C.
   112	
   113	Module-level state:
   114	
   115	```python
   116	# (session.csrf, task_id) -> (claim token, trial_id)
   117	_CLAIMS: dict[tuple[str, str], tuple[str, str]] = {}
   118	```
   119	
   120	Fixture-clearing: tests add an autouse fixture that clears `_CLAIMS`
   121	between tests, mirroring the implementer module.
   122	
   123	The router is included **unconditionally** in `make_app` (no repo
   124	gate). Navigation in `base.html` gains a permanent "evaluator" link
   125	(no `evaluator_enabled` guard), reflecting that the evaluator
   126	module needs no service-level prerequisite beyond what the planner
   127	already requires.
   128	
   129	### ┬¦A.1 Artifact trust boundary
   130	
   131	The evaluator's draft view reuses
   132	`routes/_helpers.read_proposal_rationale(proposal, artifacts_dir)`
   133	to surface the proposal's rationale inline when (a) `artifacts_uri`
   134	is `file://`, (b) the resolved path is contained within the UI
   135	service's `--artifacts-dir`, (c) the file is Ōēż 1 MiB. Any other
   136	shape renders link-only. The helper was added in chunk 9c; chunk 9d
   137	adds **no new helper** ŌĆö the same security envelope applies.
   138	
   139	The **trial's own** `artifacts_uri` and `description` MAY be set by
   140	the implementer on a successful `starting` trial (per
   141	`spec/v0/03-roles.md` ┬¦3.2 step 3). The chunk-9c implementer module
   142	already wires `description` into `Trial(...)` from its form input;
   143	`trial.artifacts_uri` is reserved for a future implementer-side
   144	artifact-upload feature. The evaluator's draft page therefore
   145	renders both `trial.description` (when set, as a read-only block)
   146	and `trial.artifacts_uri` (when set, with the chunk-9c scheme
   147	allowlist applied: only `http`, `https`, and `file` schemes are
   148	hyperlinked; any other scheme renders as `<code>` plus
   149	"(unrenderable scheme)"). When `trial.artifacts_uri` is a `file://`
   150	URI inside `--artifacts-dir` and Ōēż 1 MiB, the helper inlines the
   151	content ŌĆö same envelope as the proposal rationale.
   152	
   153	The submission's `artifacts_uri` text input is **not** hyperlinked
   154	on the confirmation page ŌĆö it renders as a plain `<code>` block.
   155	Hyperlinking a URL the operator just typed risks the same
   156	scheme-injection class lens 10 in
   157	`feedback_impl_review_lenses.md` flagged for the proposal's
   158	`artifacts_uri`. We avoid the question entirely by not rendering it
   159	as `<a href>`. (If the operator wants to follow it, they can copy
   160	it.)
   161	
   162	### ┬¦A.2 `trial_id` ownership
   163	
   164	The evaluator's `trial_id` is **server-pinned via the task
   165	payload**, not generated by the UI:
   166	
   167	- `EvaluateTask.payload.trial_id` is the trial under evaluation;
   168	  the orchestrator put it there at task-creation time.
   169	- At claim, `routes/evaluator.claim` reads
   170	  `task.payload.trial_id` and stashes it in `_CLAIMS` alongside
   171	  the claim token.
   172	- `routes/evaluator.draft_form` and `routes/evaluator.submit` look
   173	  up `trial_id` from `_CLAIMS` (keyed on
   174	  `(session.csrf, task_id)`). The rendered form has no
   175	  `name="trial_id"` input.
   176	- `routes/evaluator.submit` builds
   177	  `EvaluateSubmission(trial_id=trial_id, ŌĆ”)` from the `_CLAIMS`
   178	  entry. A forged `trial_id` form value is ignored.
   179	
   180	This mirrors chunk 9c's lens ŌĆö the request surface never carries
   181	the canonical `trial_id`. The chunk-9c memory
   182	`feedback_impl_review_lenses.md` (lens-10 sibling: "trial_id
   183	non-leak") applies unchanged.
   184	
   185	### ┬¦A.3 Metrics validation parity
   186	
   187	The evaluator submission's `metrics` dict must satisfy:
   188	
   189	1. Keys are a subset of `experiment_config.metrics_schema.root`.
   190	   The form's per-metric inputs are *generated* from
   191	   `metrics_schema` so a well-behaved browser cannot submit a key
   192	   outside the schema ŌĆö but the form parser still rejects unknown
   193	   names (a hand-crafted POST is the only way they appear).
   194	2. Each present value matches its declared `MetricType`:
   195	   - `integer` ŌĆö Python `int` (rejects `bool`, rejects `1.5`).
   196	   - `real`    ŌĆö Python `float`, finite (rejects `bool`, rejects
   197	                 `NaN` / `┬▒inf`).
   198	   - `text`    ŌĆö Python `str`.
   199	3. Empty form-input fields are treated as **omitted** (the metric
   200	   is left out of the dict, not stored as `None`).
   201	4. `status="success"` requires `len(metrics) >= 1` (UI-side
   202	   guardrail; spec allows empty).
   203	
   204	The wire (per `spec/v0/02-data-model.md` ┬¦1.3) also permits
   205	explicit `null` values for any declared metric ("when the
   206	evaluator declined to report"). The chunk-9d UI is **deliberately
   207	narrower** than the wire on this dimension: a blank form input
   208	omits the metric from the dict entirely instead of transmitting an
   209	explicit null. This is wire-legal (a subset of declared keys is
   210	allowed), keeps the form-and-payload parity simple, and matches
   211	how the scripted evaluator host already behaves. If a future use
   212	case needs to distinguish "I have no value" from "I declare null",
   213	the form gains a third option per metric (`<value> | omit |
   214	null`) and `EvaluateDraft.metrics` widens to
   215	`dict[str, int | float | str | None]`. Out of scope for 9d.
   216	
   217	The Pydantic-bound `EvaluateSubmission.metrics: dict[str, Any]
   218	| None = None` accepts whatever Python types we put in. The
   219	authoritative validation is `Store._validate_metrics`, which
   220	`store.submit` calls before transitioning the task. The form
   221	parser duplicates the spec's rules so the operator gets clean
   222	field-level errors instead of a wire-error banner; on the
   223	*server* side, `store.submit` is the trust boundary and will
   224	raise `InvalidPrecondition` on any drift.
   225	
   226	This is symmetric with how chunk 9c did ┬¦3.3 reachability twice
   227	(form-time + storage-time): cleaner UX, server still authoritative.
   228	
   229	## ┬¦B Forms helper
   230	
   231	`reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/forms.py` gains:
   232	
   233	```python
   234	@dataclass(frozen=True)
   235	class EvaluateDraft:
   236	    """Validated evaluator-form input.
   237	
   238	    The route handler combines this with the server-owned
   239	    ``trial_id`` (from ``_CLAIMS``) to construct the
   240	    ``EvaluateSubmission`` object. There is no ``description``
   241	    field ŌĆö the evaluator's submission shape per
   242	    ``spec/v0/03-roles.md`` ┬¦4.4 does not carry one.
   243	    """
   244	
   245	    status: Literal["success", "error", "eval_error"]
   246	    metrics: dict[str, int | float | str]   # only present-and-valid keys
   247	    artifacts_uri: str | None
   248	
   249	
   250	def parse_evaluate_form(
   251	    *,
   252	    metrics_schema: MetricsSchema,
   253	    status_raw: str,
   254	    metric_inputs: Mapping[str, str],   # key -> raw form value, one per schema entry
   255	    artifacts_uri_raw: str,
   256	) -> tuple[EvaluateDraft | None, FormErrors]:
   257	    ...
   258	```
   259	
   260	Validation rules:

exec
/bin/zsh -lc "nl -ba /Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9d-evaluator-module.md | sed -n '261,620p'" in /Users/ericalt/Documents/eden
 succeeded in 0ms:
   261	
   262	- `status` must be one of `{"success", "error", "eval_error"}`;
   263	  anything else ŌåÆ `errors.add(0, "status", ŌĆ”)` and `(None, errors)`.
   264	- Each `metric_inputs[name]`:
   265	  - empty/whitespace ŌåÆ omitted from the result dict (no error).
   266	  - present + non-empty:
   267	    - `metrics_schema.root[name] == "integer"`: parse with `int(s)`,
   268	      reject explicit `bool` (Python `bool` is `int`; the form-side
   269	      input is always a string so this isn't reachable, but the
   270	      parser checks `s.lower() not in ("true", "false")` to reject
   271	      a hand-crafted POST that puts `True` in an integer field).
   272	    - `"real"`: parse with `float(s)`, reject `nan`/`inf`/`-inf`
   273	      via `math.isfinite` (mirroring `Store._validate_metrics`).
   274	    - `"text"`: keep as `s.strip()` (non-empty after strip required;
   275	      an all-whitespace input is treated as omitted).
   276	  - any unknown key in `metric_inputs` outside `metrics_schema.root`
   277	    ŌåÆ `errors.add(0, name, "metric not in schema")`. (Note: the
   278	    template only emits inputs for schema keys, so this only
   279	    triggers on a hand-crafted POST.)
   280	- `status == "success"` requires `len(metrics) >= 1`; otherwise
   281	  `errors.add_overall("status=success requires at least one
   282	  metric value")`.
   283	- `artifacts_uri_raw.strip()` ŌåÆ `None` if empty. No URI shape check
   284	  at form time (the spec doesn't constrain it); the operator is
   285	  responsible for typing a sensible URI.
   286	
   287	If any error accumulated, return `(None, errors)`; otherwise
   288	`(EvaluateDraft(...), FormErrors())`.
   289	
   290	## ┬¦C Request flow
   291	
   292	Phases (numbering kept for parity with 9c, even though we have
   293	fewer):
   294	
   295	1. **Validate** the form.
   296	   - `parse_evaluate_form` returns `(None, errors)` ŌåÆ re-render
   297	     the draft template with 400, errors, and `form_state` so
   298	     the operator's input is preserved.
   299	2. **Phase 1 ŌĆö `store.submit`** with retry-before-orphan +
   300	   committed-state read-back. The exception classification differs
   301	   from chunk 9c's by design (see ┬¦C-rationale):
   302	   - 3 attempts total, backoff `(0.05, 0.2, 0.5)`.
   303	   - **Definitive short-circuits** (no retry, no read-back):
   304	     - `ConflictingResubmission` ŌåÆ orphan
   305	       `recovery_kind="conflict"`. By spec ┬¦4.2 this means a
   306	       different non-equivalent payload is already on file; no
   307	       transport ambiguity.
   308	     - `WrongToken` ŌåÆ orphan `recovery_kind="auto"`. The store
   309	       only raises `WrongToken` when `task.state == "claimed"`
   310	       but our token doesn't match, which means the claim was
   311	       reclaimed under us. A successful prior submit would have
   312	       moved the task to `submitted` *with our token preserved*
   313	       (`Store.submit` never clears the claim on success), so
   314	       `WrongToken` rules out "we won and the response was lost."
   315	     - `InvalidPrecondition` ŌåÆ form re-render (400) with the
   316	       wire-error banner, NOT an orphan. The operator can fix
   317	       the metrics and resubmit; orphaning a fixable form
   318	       failure would be hostile UX.
   319	   - **Read-back-required failures** (skip remaining retries,
   320	     jump to the read-back block below):
   321	     - `IllegalTransition` ŌĆö the store raises this when
   322	       `task.state` is not in `{"claimed", "submitted"}` at
   323	       call time. After a transport-indeterminate first attempt,
   324	       the task may be `pending` (sweeper reclaimed ŌåÆ we lost),
   325	       `completed` / `failed` (orchestrator already terminalized
   326	       ŌåÆ we won), or `submitted` by another claimant
   327	       (conflict). The read-back distinguishes these. **This is
   328	       a deliberate departure from the chunk-9c implementer
   329	       module's short-circuit pattern**, which mis-classifies a
   330	       lost-response-then-orchestrator-terminalization as an
   331	       orphan; see ┬¦K-2 for the parallel fix needed in 9c.
   332	   - **Transport-shaped exceptions** (any `Exception` not in the
   333	     four above) are retried with backoff; on exhaustion, jump
   334	     to the read-back block.
   335	3. **Read-back block.** `store.read_task(task_id)` +
   336	   `store.read_submission(task_id)` + `submissions_equivalent`.
   337	   Decisions:
   338	   - `task.state == "claimed"` and `task.claim.token == our token`
   339	     ŌåÆ orphan `recovery_kind="auto"` ("transport failure;
   340	     retry safe ŌĆö claim still ours, sweeper will reclaim eventually").
   341	   - `task.state == "claimed"` but our token is gone ŌåÆ orphan
   342	     `recovery_kind="auto"` (`eden://error/wrong-token`) ŌĆö same
   343	     prose; the prior reclaim already invalidated us.
   344	   - `task.state in {"submitted", "completed", "failed"}`:
   345	     - `read_submission` returns `None` ŌåÆ orphan
   346	       `recovery_kind="transport"` ("store invariant violation").
   347	       Implementation-illegal but defensively handled.
   348	     - `submissions_equivalent(prior, our)` ŌåÆ success page (200).
   349	       (Note: `EvaluateSubmission` equivalence keys off
   350	       `status + trial_id + metrics`; `artifacts_uri` is **not**
   351	       part of equivalence per chapter 04 ┬¦4.2 + the
   352	       `submissions_equivalent` impl. The first submission's
   353	       `artifacts_uri` wins.)
   354	     - non-equivalent ŌåÆ orphan `recovery_kind="conflict"`
   355	       (`eden://error/conflicting-resubmission`).
   356	   - `task.state == "pending"` ŌåÆ orphan `recovery_kind="auto"`
   357	     ("task reclaimed before our submit committed; retry safe by
   358	     re-claiming the task").
   359	   - `read_task` itself raises ŌåÆ orphan
   360	     `recovery_kind="transport"` (read-back probe failure).
   361	
   362	### ┬¦C-rationale ŌĆö why `IllegalTransition` is not a definitive short-circuit
   363	
   364	`Store.submit` raises `IllegalTransition` when
   365	`task.state Ōłē {"claimed", "submitted"}` at the moment of the call
   366	(`reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/_base.py` ~L593).
   367	After the route's first transport-indeterminate `submit` call, the
   368	task may have moved to:
   369	
   370	- `completed` / `failed` ŌĆö our prior call committed and the
   371	  orchestrator's terminal transition fired. Read-back finds an
   372	  equivalent recorded submission ŌåÆ success.
   373	- `pending` ŌĆö the sweeper reclaimed our claim before our prior
   374	  call committed. Read-back finds no submission ŌåÆ orphan auto.
   375	- `submitted` by *another* worker (vanishing race) ŌĆö read-back
   376	  finds a non-equivalent submission ŌåÆ conflict.
   377	
   378	Treating `IllegalTransition` as a definitive orphan would
   379	mis-classify the first case (we won) as an orphan. The simplest
   380	correct fix is to route `IllegalTransition` into the read-back
   381	arm where the actual outcome is determined.
   382	
   383	`WrongToken` and `ConflictingResubmission` *are* definitive:
   384	`WrongToken` requires `task.state == "claimed"` with a
   385	non-matching token (which never happens after a successful prior
   386	submit, because successful submit preserves our token), and
   387	`ConflictingResubmission` is the spec-specified definitive
   388	"different payload won" signal.
   389	
   390	The single-step structure means there's no Phase-1-failed /
   391	Phase-2-failed split. The submit either succeeds, definitively
   392	fails (rendered as a form error or orphan), or transport-fails
   393	into the read-back arm.
   394	
   395	### ┬¦C-recovery (per-error)
   396	
   397	| Outcome | Definition | UI rendering | Operator action |
   398	|---|---|---|---|
   399	| ok | submit returned cleanly OR retry returned cleanly OR read-back found equivalent prior submission | `evaluator_submitted.html`, 200 | none |
   400	| InvalidPrecondition (form-time, e.g. metric type drift only the server caught) | server rejected the metrics shape | re-render draft with the wire-error banner attached | fix the metrics and resubmit |
   401	| WrongToken | the prior reclaim invalidated our claim (sweeper or operator) | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | none ŌĆö prior reclaim already restored task to `pending` |
   402	| IllegalTransition | task was reclaimed/terminalized before our submit landed | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | none |
   403	| ConflictingResubmission | a different submission won the race for this task | orphan, `recovery_kind="conflict"` | operator triage; the system's record stands |
   404	| transport, retry exhausted, claim still ours | network glitch persisted; claim TTL will eventually reclaim | orphan, `recovery_kind="auto"` | wait for TTL, or operator-side reclaim |
   405	| transport, retry exhausted, server committed equivalent | "submitted, response lost" sub-case A | success page (treated as `ok`) | none |
   406	| transport, retry exhausted, server committed non-equivalent | "different submission won" sub-case A' | orphan, `recovery_kind="conflict"` | operator triage |
   407	| transport, retry exhausted, store invariant violated | implementation-illegal: terminal task with no recorded submission | orphan, `recovery_kind="transport"` | operator investigation |
   408	| transport, retry exhausted, read-back probe itself failed | indeterminate | orphan, `recovery_kind="transport"` | operator investigation |
   409	
   410	Key contrast with chunk 9c: there is **no orphaned `starting`
   411	trial** to worry about. The evaluator never creates a trial; the
   412	trial already existed when the evaluate task was created. So the
   413	"sweeper composite-commits the trial to error on reclaim" recovery
   414	branch from 9c does not apply here. On reclaim of an evaluate task
   415	with an orphaned submit, `_base.reclaim` reverts the task from
   416	`claimed ŌåÆ pending`; the trial stays `starting` and a fresh
   417	evaluate task can be created (per ┬¦4.4 retry semantics). No trial-
   418	level recovery is needed.
   419	
   420	## ┬¦D Templates
   421	
   422	Four new templates under
   423	`reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/`:
   424	
   425	- `evaluator_list.html` ŌĆö pending evaluate tasks (table of
   426	  task_id + trial_id), recent trials panel, link-back to
   427	  `/evaluator/<task_id>/claim`. Banner from
   428	  `?banner=ŌĆ”` query param.
   429	- `evaluator_claim.html` ŌĆö read-only trial context:
   430	  - **Trial fields**: trial_id, branch, commit_sha,
   431	    parent_commits, status, started_at. The commit_sha and branch
   432	    are the load-bearing fields ŌĆö they tell the operator what to
   433	    check out from the bare repo.
   434	  - **Trial-side optional fields set by the implementer per
   435	    `spec/v0/03-roles.md` ┬¦3.2 step 3**: `trial.description`
   436	    (rendered as a read-only `<pre>` block when set);
   437	    `trial.artifacts_uri` rendered with the chunk-9c scheme
   438	    allowlist + read-only inline rendering when it's a `file://`
   439	    inside `--artifacts-dir`.
   440	  - **Proposal context**: proposal slug + priority +
   441	    artifacts_uri (chunk-9c scheme allowlist) + rationale block
   442	    (inline via `read_proposal_rationale`, or a rationale-not-
   443	    rendered note).
   444	  - **Operator instructions** (informational): a short
   445	    "to evaluate this trial, fetch the bare repo and check out
   446	    `{{ commit_sha }}` on a worktree of your own; run your eval
   447	    procedure; come back here and fill in the metrics" preamble.
   448	    No git command prefilled ŌĆö the bare-repo location is a
   449	    deployment concern (Phase 10 compose stack pins it; in dev,
   450	    the operator knows the path).
   451	
   452	  Then the form:
   453	  - status radio (success / error / eval_error)
   454	  - one input per metric in `metrics_schema.root`, labeled with
   455	    metric name + declared type (`integer` / `real` / `text`).
   456	    `<input type="number" step="1">` for integer, `<input
   457	    type="number" step="any">` for real, `<input type="text">` for
   458	    text. (`type="number"` is browser-side UX; the server still
   459	    parses string form values.)
   460	  - optional `artifacts_uri` text input (no scheme allowlist ŌĆö
   461	    plain text, `<input type="text">`)
   462	  - `csrf_token` hidden field
   463	  - submit button
   464	- `evaluator_submitted.html` ŌĆö confirmation: task_id, trial_id,
   465	  status, metrics dict (rendered as a small definition list),
   466	  submission's `artifacts_uri` as plain `<code>` (NOT hyperlinked,
   467	  per ┬¦A.1).
   468	- `evaluator_orphaned.html` ŌĆö three case-specific blocks
   469	  matching `recovery_kind`:
   470	  - `auto` ŌĆö "the orchestrator's reclaim sweeper will return the
   471	    task to `pending` once the claim TTL expires; the trial
   472	    itself remains in `starting` and a fresh evaluate task can
   473	    be created." (No mention of trial-level reclaim ŌĆö distinct
   474	    from the implementer orphan template, which spoke of trial
   475	    composite-commit-to-error. The evaluator never creates a
   476	    trial.)
   477	  - `conflict` ŌĆö "a different submission was already committed for
   478	    this task; the system's record stands. If your submission
   479	    should be the one kept, an operator-side replay through
   480	    admin reclaim is needed (Phase 9e)."
   481	  - `transport` ŌĆö "transport failure left the outcome unknown;
   482	    operator investigation needed. Possible causes: read-back
   483	    probe failed; store invariant violated (terminal task with
   484	    no recorded submission)."
   485	- `base.html` ŌĆö add a permanent `<a href="/evaluator/">evaluator</a>`
   486	  navigation link alongside `planner` and the conditional
   487	  `implementer`. No conditional gate.
   488	
   489	## ┬¦E Reused chunk-1 / 9c surface
   490	
   491	- `_helpers.csrf_ok`, `_helpers.get_session`,
   492	  `_helpers.is_htmx_request`, `_helpers.read_proposal_rationale`.
   493	- `forms.FormErrors` (no changes; mode is now also single-row).
   494	- `_CLAIMS`-pattern dict (per-route, not shared across routes;
   495	  the implementer's `_CLAIMS` and the evaluator's `_CLAIMS` are
   496	  separate module-level dicts to avoid cross-module key collision
   497	  on `task_id` if the same operator's session is mid-claim on
   498	  both kinds simultaneously).
   499	- The wire-error banner mapping (`_ERROR_NAMES`) is duplicated in
   500	  `evaluator.py` (private to the module) rather than extracted ŌĆö
   501	  it's 4 entries; an extraction now would be premature. (Marked
   502	  in ┬¦K-1 as a lukewarm follow-up, not a blocker.)
   503	- The retry policy constants (`_RETRY_DELAYS_S = (0.05, 0.2, 0.5)`)
   504	  are duplicated for the same reason.
   505	- `_iso(dt)` (Zulu suffix) is duplicated.
   506	
   507	(All three duplications are identical bytes between
   508	`routes/planner.py`, `routes/implementer.py`, and the new
