   667	
   668	4. **`test_evaluator_security.py`** ŌĆö invariants.
   669	   - Bearer token never appears in any rendered HTML or
   670	     `Set-Cookie` header on `/evaluator/*` routes.
   671	   - CSRF mismatch returns 403 on each mutating route (claim,
   672	     submit).
   673	   - Cookie attributes (HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax, Path=/, Secure
   674	     opt-in) hold for the evaluator client.
   675	   - `trial_id` is server-only:
   676	     - `name="trial_id"` and `id="trial_id"` are absent from the
   677	       rendered draft form.
   678	     - A forged `trial_id` form value is ignored: the recorded
   679	       submission's `trial_id` matches the task payload's
   680	       `trial_id`, not the form value.
   681	   - The submission's `artifacts_uri` is rendered as plain
   682	     `<code>` on the confirmation page (NOT inside an `<a href>`),
   683	     even when the operator typed a `javascript:` URI.
   684	   - The proposal's `artifacts_uri` rendering on the draft page
   685	     reuses the chunk-9c scheme allowlist (only http/https/file
   686	     hyperlinked); a `javascript:` URI on the proposal renders
   687	     as `<code>` + "(unrenderable scheme)".
   688	   - The trial's `artifacts_uri` rendering on the draft page
   689	     also applies the scheme allowlist; a `javascript:` URI on
   690	     the trial renders as `<code>` + "(unrenderable scheme)".
   691	   - The trial's `description` is rendered escaped (default
   692	     Jinja2 autoescape); a `<script>` payload in
   693	     `trial.description` shows as text, not executed.
   694	
   695	5. **`test_evaluator_e2e.py`** ŌĆö `pytest.mark.e2e` two-process
   696	   test against a real `eden_task_store_server` subprocess.
   697	   - Forks the task-store-server on an ephemeral port.
   698	   - Constructs the web-ui app pointing at that server's
   699	     `StoreClient`.
   700	   - Seeds: a ready proposal ŌåÆ an implement task ŌåÆ
   701	     `_accept_implement` (or direct test helper) to push the trial
   702	     to `starting` with a `commit_sha` set ŌåÆ an evaluate task.
   703	     (Or: simulate the orchestrator's pieces via direct store
   704	     calls; we don't need a real implementer host running.)
   705	   - Drives a TestClient through claim ŌåÆ submit (status=success
   706	     with a valid metric).
   707	   - Asserts that `read_range` on the wire shows the
   708	     `task.submitted` event with the evaluator submission's
   709	     metrics. Tears down with SIGTERM ŌåÆ SIGKILL fallback.
   710	
