   740	
   741	## ┬¦K Known follow-ups
   742	
   743	- **┬¦K-1.** The duplicated `_RETRY_DELAYS_S`, `_iso`,
   744	  `_ERROR_NAMES`, `_wire_error_banner`, `_render_orphaned`-style
   745	  helpers across `routes/planner.py`, `routes/implementer.py`,
   746	  and `routes/evaluator.py` are now three copies of the same
   747	  bytes. Phase 9e is the natural extraction point; doing it now
   748	  would diff against three modules at once and obscure 9d's
   749	  surface in code review.
   750	- **┬¦K-2.** Apply the ┬¦C-rationale `IllegalTransition`-feeds-
   751	  read-back fix to the chunk-9c implementer module (and the
   752	  chunk-1 planner module if it has the same shape). The
   753	  implementer's `_retry_submit_with_readback` currently
   754	  short-circuits `IllegalTransition` to `recovery_kind="auto"`,
   755	  which mis-classifies "we won and the orchestrator
   756	  terminalized before our retry got a clean response" as an
   757	  orphan. The fix is mechanical (move the `except
   758	  IllegalTransition` arm to fall through to read-back instead
   759	  of returning early); the test changes are a new sub-case in
   760	  `test_implementer_partial_write.py` that drives the task to
   761	  `completed` between attempts and asserts the success page
   762	  renders. Doing this in 9d's PR would conflate scopes; doing
   763	  it in a follow-up PR right after 9d merges is cleanest. Same
   764	  treatment for the planner if the planner has the equivalent
   765	  short-circuit.
   766	- **┬¦K-3.** Per-metric required/optional signaling: the
   767	  metrics_schema today is `dict[str, MetricType]` (no
   768	  required/optional bit per metric). If experiments later want
   769	  to mark a metric as required for `status=success`, that's a
   770	  spec-level change to `metrics-schema.schema.json` + meta-schema
   771	  plus the form generator. Out of scope for 9d.
   772	- **┬¦K-4.** No "rerun the scripted evaluator on this trial"
   773	  trigger button. The Phase 9e observability story is the
   774	  natural place: an admin can re-create an evaluate task for a
   775	  trial, and the scripted evaluator host will pick it up.
   776	- **┬¦K-5.** Explicit-null metric submission. The chunk-9d UI
   777	  treats blank inputs as "metric omitted from the submission";
   778	  the wire (per `spec/v0/02-data-model.md` ┬¦1.3) also permits
   779	  explicit `null`. If a future use case needs the distinction,
   780	  see ┬¦A.3 for the upgrade path.
   781	
   782	## Verification
   783	
   784	Before declaring done:
   785	
   786	1. `uv run ruff check .` clean.
   787	2. `uv run pyright` clean.
   788	3. `uv run pytest -q` runs the full suite; all five new evaluator
   789	   test files green.
   790	4. `uv run pytest -m e2e` includes the new evaluator e2e and
   791	   continues to pass the existing implementer + planner e2e tests.
   792	5. `npx --yes markdownlint-cli2@0.14.0 ŌĆ”` clean for the new
   793	   README sections.
   794	6. Manual smoke test: bring up
   795	   `eden_task_store_server` + `eden_orchestrator` (so the
   796	   implementer host's `_accept_implement` path is wired) +
   797	   `eden_implementer_host` and seed an evaluate task; open
   798	   `/evaluator/` in a browser, claim the task, fill in metrics,
   799	   submit; observe a 200 confirmation page and confirm the
   800	   trial transitions to `success` after the orchestrator
   801	   terminalization.
   802	
   803	## Execution order
   804	
   805	1. Add `parse_evaluate_form` + `EvaluateDraft` to `forms.py`.
   806	2. Create `routes/evaluator.py` with the four routes and the
   807	   shared `_retry_submit_with_readback` helper.
   808	3. Wire `routes.evaluator.router` into `make_app` unconditionally;
   809	   remove the no-op gate (the evaluator does not need `repo`).
   810	4. Add the four templates + the navigation link in `base.html`.
   811	5. Add `seed_evaluate_task` to `conftest.py`.
   812	6. Write the five test files.
   813	7. Run the full local verification suite (┬¦Verification).
   814	8. Update `reference/services/web-ui/README.md`, `AGENTS.md`,
   815	   `reference/README.md`, `docs/roadmap.md`.
   816	9. Run `/codex-review` on the implementation; iterate to
   817	   convergence.
   818	10. `/codify` lessons learned.
   819	11. Commit + PR + merge.
   820	
   821	## Risks / things to watch
   822	
   823	- **Metrics-form parser drift from `Store._validate_metrics`.**
   824	  The form's per-type parsing (integer rejects floats, real
   825	  rejects non-finite, no bools) must stay in sync with what the
   826	  store would reject. The mitigation is a parametrized test in
   827	  `test_evaluator_routes.py` that walks every reject branch the
   828	  store has and confirms the form rejects it identically. If a
   829	  future spec change adds a new metric type, both the form
   830	  parser and the store validator must update; a parity test
   831	  similar to `test_schema_parity.py` would be ideal but is out of
   832	  scope here (the metrics-schema is small and the symmetry is
   833	  hand-maintained).
   834	- **Sub-case A' test mock symmetry.** The 9c codified pattern
   835	  (`feedback_retry_readback_test_mocks.md`) requires
   836	  commit-AND-raise on every call. For sub-case A' the call must
   837	  also drive a *different* terminal state in between, which the
   838	  test does via direct `store.accept(...)` calls. Easy to mis-
   839	  write; the codified memory's "How to apply" section covers it.
   840	- **`status=success` zero-metric guardrail.** The spec allows
   841	  empty metrics as a "subset"; we tighten that at the UI layer.
   842	  If a future spec chapter explicitly says zero-metric success
   843	  is wire-legal, the UI guard should remain (it's still bad UX)
   844	  but the e2e test should cover the wire-legal-but-UI-rejected
   845	  case to ensure our policy is intentional, not a bug.
   846	- **Conflict-page prose vs. claim-still-ours prose.** Sub-cases B
   847	  and the read-back-pending-state branch both render
   848	  `recovery_kind="auto"`, but the underlying state is different
   849	  (claim still ours vs. claim already invalidated vs. task
   850	  already reclaimed). All three render the same template arm;
   851	  the banner is the differentiator. Lens-10 of
   852	  `feedback_impl_review_lenses.md` (state-prose
   853	  synchronization) calls this exact pattern out ŌĆö assertions in
   854	  `test_evaluator_partial_write.py` check the *banner string*,
   855	  not just `recovery_kind`, so we don't paper over the
   856	  distinction.
   857	- **Trial-existence assumption at draft time.** If the trial that
   858	  the evaluate task references is somehow gone (deleted by an
   859	  operator, store corruption), the draft form crashes on
   860	  `read_trial`. The implementation catches `DispatchError` and
   861	  renders the wire-error page (502), mirroring 9c. Probably fine;
   862	  the operator's recovery is to investigate the orchestrator log.
   863	
