    19	### 1.3 Metric values
    20	
    21	A metric value is one of: a JSON number (for `integer` or `real` types), a JSON string (for `text` type), or `null` (when the evaluator declined to report). Implementations MUST reject metric values whose JSON type does not match the declared metrics-schema type.
    22	
    23	The `integer` and `real` metric types both travel the wire as JSON numbers; they are distinguished by what values each admits:
    24	
    25	- **`integer`** ŌĆö a JSON number whose value is an integer (no fractional component). Wire forms such as `3`, `-7`, or `1.0` are accepted; `1.5` MUST be rejected. A conforming orchestrator MUST validate this constraint when persisting a metrics payload.
    26	- **`real`** ŌĆö any JSON number, including values with a fractional component.
    27	- **`text`** ŌĆö a JSON string.
    28	- **`null`** ŌĆö allowed for any declared type when the evaluator declined to report that metric.
